Post-audit-mirror build note (d20b0aed — UNAUDITED relative to the snapshot)
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
As of branch `chore/panoptic-v2-forge-install`, the demo no longer compiles against
the vendored `contracts/panoptic-borrowed/` audit snapshot. The Solidity build is
forge-installed from the canonical mirror `lib/panoptic-v2-core` pinned at commit
`d20b0aed127ab5d3e5ca17c5399782aad2f0ff4c` (post-audit `main`). This is POST-AUDIT
code: it carries changes made AFTER the Code4rena snapshot fe55774 and is therefore
UNAUDITED relative to that snapshot. The demo's behavioral assertions (WRAP-01..04)
were re-run green against d20b0aed without weakening any proof.

Behavioral / ABI deltas vs the audited snapshot fe55774 reconciled in this port:
  1. Contracts renamed: PanopticPool→PanopticPoolV2, CollateralTracker→CollateralTrackerV2,
     SemiFungiblePositionManager→SemiFungiblePositionManagerV4, PanopticFactory→PanopticFactoryV4.
  2. PanopticPoolV2 / CollateralTrackerV2 now inherit TransientReentrancyGuard (EIP-1153
     transient-storage reentrancy guard). The dispatch/dispatchFrom reentrancy paths exercised
     by the settleLong / forceExercise / liquidation proofs remain green under it.
  3. CollateralTrackerV2() constructor dropped its flat commission-fee arg (vendored
     CT_COMMISSION_FEE=10). Commission is now a RiskParameters-driven notional/premium fee
     resolved through the RiskEngine — a behavioral change in fee derivation, not just a signature.
  4. PanopticPool read renamed+extended: getAccumulatedFeesAndPositionsData →
     getFullPositionsData, with two appended return values (collateralRequirements,
     netPremiaPerPosition). The first three returns are byte-identical; the streamia seam
     consumes only longPremium, so the swap-seam (IPanopticData) is preserved.
  5. types/TokenId.sol added a riskPartnerIndex validation
     (reverts Errors.InvalidTokenIdParameter(3) when riskPartnerIndex > numLegs-1). The
     demo's TokenId construction satisfies it without modification (all wrapper open/mint
     proofs pass), so no test TokenId had to be rebuilt.

Single-compile note (intentional, not a gap)
---------------------------------------------
FORK-01's roadmap wording references a multi-version solc matrix; 07-RESEARCH §5
retired it — Panoptic V2 is `^0.8.24` for every file, so this repo uses a single
`evm_version="cancun"` / `solc 0.8.24` compile profile. This is intentional, not a gap.
